<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,776,1089]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,957,981]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</emphasis>
Described on the basis of two males and four females. The second, and hitherto last known record of this species is from Antiparos Island, with one male and two females. It is the only known 
<taxonomicName box="[1219,1373,993,1017]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1219,1373,993,1017]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Antiparos, and one of the two known 
<taxonomicName box="[590,744,1029,1053]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[590,744,1029,1053]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Megaphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from Naxos; the other is 
<taxonomicName authority="Mauries &amp; Karamaouna, 1984" authorityName="Mauries &amp; Karamaouna" authorityYear="1984" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bicolor" subSpecies="crassiflagellum">
<emphasis box="[1133,1435,1029,1053]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M. bicolor crassiflagellum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mauries" box="[158,505,1065,1089]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refString="Mauries, J - P. &amp; Karamaouna, M. (1984) Myriapodes-Diplopodes nouveaux et peu connus des iles Naxos, Paros et Antiparos (Cyclades, Grece). Biologia gallo-hellenica, 11, 51 - 59." type="journal article" year="1984">
Mauriès &amp; Karamaouna, 
<number box="[445,505,1065,1089]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
